---

# 4. Load Configuration

The Hypervisor SHALL:

* load configuration files;
* apply environment overrides;
* validate required fields;
* initialize default values.

Startup SHALL abort on configuration errors.

---

# 5. Initialize Core

Core initialization SHALL create:

* logger;
* configuration manager;
* dependency injection container;
* internal event bus;
* lifecycle manager.

No business services are started during this phase.

---

# 6. Open Storage

The Hypervisor SHALL:

* establish database connections;
* verify connectivity;
* verify schema compatibility.

Startup SHALL abort if persistent storage is unavailable.

---

# 7. Run Migrations

Pending schema migrations SHALL execute before any service initialization.

Failed migrations SHALL abort startup.

Partial migrations are prohibited.

---

# 8. Construct Services

Services SHALL be created through dependency injection.

Construction order SHALL respect dependency direction.

